alternatives.transcript: doing well this morning a sixty two year old man came into the ed this morning name is leslie palmer he presented the ed with shortness of breath and fatigue that has been worsening over the last six months state that states that his shortness of breath happens at rest and gets worse with any physical activity his vitals were his heart rate was ninety his respiration rate was twenty two bp was eighty or fifty and o two stats were down low at eighty six percent he has a past medical history of afib hypertension hyperlipidemia and diabetes he has had a triple bypass in the in the past and five stents his mom died of breast cancer his dad currently has alzheimer's he's a pack a day smoker in good health good diet good exercise no alcohol or drugs he has a long list of medication atorvastatin clopidogrel furosemide metoprolol lisinopril metformin and warfarin he has no known known drug allergies on his review of systems he presented with fatigue as i mentioned weight gain wheezing dyspnea orthopnea and he did present with lower extremity edema on physical exam he had jugular jugular venous distension an irregular rate with a split s two his pmi was displaced laterally he did present with rails and wheezing but no chest wall tenderness and he did present with pedal edema on his chest x-ray it showed cardiomegaly and pulmonary edema his echo showed dcm with left ventricular ejection fraction of less than thirty percent and his ekg showed a left bundle branch with lvh vaulted criteria his troponin was point o four and his bnp was four thousand i did diagnose him with ischemic cardiomyopathy with an nyha class four and i admitted him to the icu because of that vitals every two hours strict bed rest low sodium diet kvo fluids i kept him on his clopidogrel and his warfarin but i took him off everything else and i added dopamine iv and i put him on an insulin sliding scale i put him on bipap because his o two stats were so low i also had a ptinr because he's still on warfarin and serio troponins to make sure that's going in the correct direction and then i referred him to the interventional cardiologist for icd and crtd placement thank you so much and hope you have a good day
